						               													<description>H.D.P.: Hasta Donde Puedas is an Argentinian implementation of Cards Against Humanity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play begins with a judge, known as the H.D.P, playing a black card with a question or fill-in-the-blank phrase from the top of the deck and showing it to all players. Each player holds a hand of ten white answer cards at the beginning of each round, and passes a card to the H.D.P., face-down, representing their answer to the question on the card. The H.D.P. determines which answer card is the funniest one in the context of the question or fill-in-the-blank card. The player who submitted the chosen card is given the question card to represent a point, and then the player to the left of the H.D.P. becomes the new H.D.P. for the next round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play continues until the players agree to stop, at which point the player with the most points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
